Package grafioschtrader.entities

Class GTNetInstrumentCurrencypair

java.lang.Object
grafiosch.entities.BaseID<Integer>
grafioschtrader.entities.GTNetInstrument
grafioschtrader.entities.GTNetInstrumentCurrencypair
@Entity public class GTNetInstrumentCurrencypair extends GTNetInstrument
Instrument pool entry for currency pairs in the GT-Network. Currency pairs are identified by the combination of fromCurrency and toCurrency (both ISO 4217 codes), enabling cross-system matching. The exchange rate represents how many units of toCurrency equal one unit of fromCurrency (e.g., EUR/USD = 1.10 means 1 EUR = 1.10 USD).

Usage

  • Used by GTNetLastprice for intraday exchange rate data
  • Used by GTNetHistoryquote for historical exchange rates (foreign instruments only)
  • When instrument exists locally (JOIN matches currencypair table), historical data goes to Historyquote instead
See Also:
  • for base fields and local/foreign distinction
  • for security instruments
